cl_nettimesyncboundmode cvar method of restricting client time to valid values, 0 = no correction, 1 = tight bounding (jerky with packet loss), 2 = loose bounding (corrects it if out of bounds), 3 = leniant bounding (ignores temporary errors due to varying framerate), 4 = slow adjustment method from Quake3, 5 = slighttly nicer version of Quake3 method, 6 = bounding + Quake3 6
cl_nettimesyncboundtolerance cvar how much error is tolerated by bounding check, as a fraction of frametime, 0.25 = up to 25% margin of error tolerated, 1 = use only new time, 0 = use only old time (same effect as setting cl_nettimesyncfactor to 1) 0.25

fog cmd set global fog parameters (density red green blue [alpha [mindist [maxdist [top [fadedepth]]]]])
fog_heighttexture cmd set global fog parameters (density red green blue alpha mindist maxdist top depth textures/mapname/fogheight.tga)
force_centerview cmd recenters view (stops looking up/down)
forceqmenu cvar enables the quake menu instead of the quakec menu.dat (if present) 0
fov cvar field of vision, 1-170 degrees, default 90, some players use 110-130 100
fraglimit cvar ends level if this many frags is reached by any player 0
fraglimit_override cvar Frag limit overriding the mapinfo specified one (use 0 to play without limit, and -1 to use the mapinfo's limit) -1
freelook cvar mouse controls pitch instead of forward/back 1
fs_empty_files_in_pack_mark_deletions cvar if enabled, empty files in a pak/pk3 count as not existing but cancel the search in further packs, effectively allowing patch pak/pk3 files to 'delete' files 1
fs_gamedir cvar the list of currently selected gamedirs (use the 'gamedir' command to change this)
fs_rescan cmd rescans filesystem for new pack archives and any other changes
fullinfo cmd allows client to modify their userinfo
fullserverinfo cmd internal use only, sent by server to client to update client's local copy of serverinfo string

DarkPlaces clients retry once per second, so this should be <= 1. Failure here may lead to connect attempts failing. 0.5
net_connectfloodblockingtimeout cvar when a connection packet is received, it will block all future connect packets from that IP address for this many seconds (cuts down on connect floods). Note that this does not include retries from the same IP; these are handled earlier and let in. 5
net_connecttimeout cvar after requesting a connection, the client must reply within this many seconds or be dropped (cuts down on connect floods). Must be above 10 seconds. 30
net_getstatusfloodblockingtimeout cvar when a getstatus packet is received, it will block all future getstatus packets from that IP address for this many seconds (cuts down on getstatus floods). DarkPlaces retries every 4 seconds, and qstat retries once per second, so this should be <= 1. Failure here may lead to server not showing up in the server list. 1
net_messagetimeout cvar drops players who have not sent any packets for this many seconds 30
net_refresh cmd query dp master servers and refresh all server information
net_slist cmd query dp master servers and print all server information
net_slist_favorites cvar contains a list of IP addresses and ports to always query explicitly
net_slist_maxtries cvar how many times to ask the same server for information (more times gives better ping reports but takes longer) 3
net_slist_pause cvar when set to 1, the server list won't update until it is set back to 0 0
net_slist_queriesperframe cvar maximum number of server information requests to send each rendered frame (guards against low framerates causing problems) 4
net_slist_queriespersecond cvar how many server information requests to send per second 60
net_slist_timeout cvar how long to listen for a server information response before giving up 4
net_slistqw cmd query qw master servers and print all server information
net_sourceaddresscheck cvar compare the source IP address for replies (more secure, may break some bad multihoming setups 1
net_stats cmd print network statistics
net_test cvar internal development use only, leave it alone (usually does nothing anyway) 0
net_tos_dscp cvar DiffServ Codepoint for network sockets (may need game restart to apply) 32
net_usesizelimit cvar use packet size limiting (0: never, 1: in non-CSQC mode, 2: always) 2
nextframe alias qc_cmd_svmenu nextframe ${* ?}
nextmap cvar override the maplist when switching to the next map
nextul cmd sends next fragment of current upload buffer (screenshot for example)
noaim cvar QW option to disable vertical autoaim 1
nobots alias minplayers 0; minplayers_per_team 0
noclip cmd noclip mode (flight without collisions, move through walls)
noexit cvar kills anyone attempting to use an exit 0
nomonsters cvar unused cvar in quake, can be used by mods 0
nosound cvar disables sound 0
nospectators alias qc_cmd_sv nospectators ${* ?}
notarget cmd notarget mode (monsters do not see you)
notification_allow_chatboxprint cvar Allow INFO notifications to be printed to chat box 0 = do not allow, 1 = allow only if allowed by individual notification_INFO* cvars, 2 = force all INFO notifications to be printed to the chatbox 1

physics_ode cvar run ODE physics (VERY experimental and potentially buggy) 0
physics_ode_allowconvex cvar allow usage of Convex Hull primitive type on trimeshes that have custom 'collisionconvex' mesh. If disabled, trimesh primitive type are used. 0
physics_ode_autodisable cvar automatic disabling of objects which dont move for long period of time, makes object stacking a lot faster 1
physics_ode_autodisable_steps cvar how many steps object should be dormant to be autodisabled 10
physics_ode_autodisable_threshold_angular cvar body will be disabled if it's angular move below this value 6
physics_ode_autodisable_threshold_linear cvar body will be disabled if it's linear move below this value 0.6
physics_ode_autodisable_threshold_samples cvar average threshold with this number of samples 5
physics_ode_autodisable_time cvar how many seconds object should be dormant to be autodisabled 0
physics_ode_constantstep cvar use constant step instead of variable step which tends to increase stability, if set to 1 uses sys_ticrate, instead uses it's own value 0
physics_ode_contact_cfm cvar contact solver cfm parameter - Constraint Force Mixing (see ODE User Guide) 0
physics_ode_contact_erp cvar contact solver erp parameter - Error Restitution Percent (see ODE User Guide) 0.96
physics_ode_contact_maxpoints cvar maximal number of contact points between 2 objects, higher = stable (and slower), can be up to 32 16
physics_ode_contact_mu cvar contact solver mu parameter - friction pyramid approximation 1 (see ODE User Guide) 1
physics_ode_contactsurfacelayer cvar allows objects to overlap this many units to reduce jitter 1
physics_ode_iterationsperframe cvar divisor for time step, runs multiple physics steps per frame 1
physics_ode_movelimit cvar clamp velocity if a single move would exceed this percentage of object thickness, to prevent flying through walls, be aware that behavior depends of step type 0.5
physics_ode_printstats cvar print ODE stats each frame 0
physics_ode_quadtree_depth cvar desired subdivision level of quadtree culling space 5
physics_ode_spinlimit cvar reset spin velocity if it gets too large 10000
physics_ode_trick_fixnan cvar engine trick that checks and fixes NaN velocity/origin/angles on objects, a value of 2 makes console prints on each fix 1
physics_ode_world_cfm cvar world solver cfm parameter - Constraint Force Mixing (see ODE User Guide); not touched when -1 -1
physics_ode_world_damping cvar enabled damping scale (see ODE User Guide), this scales all damping values, be aware that behavior depends of step type 1
physics_ode_world_damping_angular cvar world angular damping scale (see ODE User Guide); use defaults when set to -1 0.05
physics_ode_world_damping_angular_threshold cvar world angular damping threshold (see ODE User Guide); use defaults when set to -1 0.1
physics_ode_world_damping_linear cvar world linear damping scale (see ODE User Guide); use defaults when set to -1 0.01
physics_ode_world_damping_linear_threshold cvar world linear damping threshold (see ODE User Guide); use defaults when set to -1 0.1
physics_ode_world_erp cvar world solver erp parameter - Error Restitution Percent (see ODE User Guide); use defaults when set to -1 -1
physics_ode_world_gravitymod cvar multiplies gravity got from sv_gravity, this may be needed to tweak if strong damping is used 1
physics_ode_worldstep_iterations cvar parameter to dWorldQuickStep 20

vid_conheight cvar virtual height of 2D graphics system 600
vid_conwidth cvar virtual width of 2D graphics system 800
vid_desktopfullscreen cvar force desktop resolution for fullscreen; also use some OS dependent tricks for better fullscreen integration 1
vid_fullscreen cvar use fullscreen (1) or windowed (0) 1
vid_gl13 cvar enables faster rendering using OpenGL 1.3 features (such as GL_ARB_texture_env_combine extension) 1
vid_gl20 cvar enables faster rendering using OpenGL 2.0 features (such as GL_ARB_fragment_shader extension) 1
vid_grabkeyboard cvar whether to grab the keyboard when mouse is active (prevents use of volume control keys, music player keys, etc on some keyboards) 0
vid_height cvar resolution 768
vid_minheight cvar minimum vid_height that is acceptable (to be set in default.cfg in mods) 0
vid_minwidth cvar minimum vid_width that is acceptable (to be set in default.cfg in mods) 0
vid_mouse cvar whether to use the mouse in windowed mode (fullscreen always does) 1
vid_netwmfullscreen cvar custom cvar 0
vid_pixelheight cvar adjusts vertical field of vision to account for non-square pixels (1280x1024 on a CRT monitor for example) 1
vid_refreshrate cvar refresh rate to use, in hz (higher values flicker less, if supported by your monitor) 60
vid_resizable cvar 0: window not resizable, 1: resizable, 2: window can be resized but the framebuffer isn't adjusted 0
vid_restart cmd restarts video system (closes and reopens the window, restarts renderer)
vid_samples cvar how many anti-aliasing samples per pixel to request from the graphics driver (4 is recommended, 1 is faster) 1
vid_soft cvar enables use of the DarkPlaces Software Rasterizer rather than OpenGL or Direct3D 0
vid_soft_interlace cvar whether the DarkPlaces Software Rasterizer should interlace the screen bands occupied by each thread 1
vid_soft_threads cvar the number of threads the DarkPlaces Software Rasterizer should use 8
vid_sRGB cvar if hardware is capable, modify rendering to be gamma corrected for the sRGB color standard (computer monitors, TVs), recommended 0
vid_sRGB_fallback cvar do an approximate sRGB fallback if not properly supported by hardware (2: also use the fallback if framebuffer is 8bit, 3: always use the fallback even if sRGB is supported) 2
vid_stereobuffer cvar enables 'quad-buffered' stereo rendering for stereo shutterglasses, HMD (head mounted display) devices, or polarized stereo LCDs, if supported by your drivers 0
vid_stick_mouse cvar have the mouse stuck in the center of the screen 0
vid_touchscreen cvar Use touchscreen-style input (no mouse grab, track mouse motion only while button is down, screen areas for mimicing joystick axes and buttons 0
vid_touchscreen_density cvar Standard quantized screen density multiplier (see Android documentation for DisplayMetrics), similar values are given on iPhoneOS 2.0
vid_touchscreen_outlinealpha cvar opacity of touchscreen area outlines 0
vid_touchscreen_overlayalpha cvar opacity of touchscreen area icons 0.25
vid_touchscreen_showkeyboard cvar shows the platform's screen keyboard for text entry, can be set by csqc or menu qc if it wants to receive text input, does nothing if the platform has no screen keyboard 0
vid_touchscreen_supportshowkeyboard cvar indicates if the platform supports a virtual keyboard 0
vid_touchscreen_xdpi cvar Horizontal DPI of the screen (only valid on Android currently) 300
vid_touchscreen_ydpi cvar Vertical DPI of the screen (only valid on Android currently) 300
vid_userefreshrate cvar set this to 1 to make vid_refreshrate used, or to 0 to let the engine choose a sane default 0
vid_vsync cvar sync to vertical blank, prevents 'tearing' (seeing part of one frame and part of another on the screen at the same time), automatically disabled when doing timedemo benchmarks 0
